# =============================================================================
# Palmeiras Korea Dashboard — environment variables (ALL OPTIONAL)
# =============================================================================
# The app + data pipeline run fully WITHOUT any keys:
#   • News           — Google News RSS (keyless)
#   • Standings      — ESPN public JSON (keyless, CURRENT season)
#   • Matches        — ESPN public JSON (keyless, CURRENT fixtures/results)
# Keys below only ENHANCE the result. Copy this file to `.env.local` (gitignored)
# and fill in any you have. Never commit real secrets.

# --- LLM (Korean summaries + "why it matters" + fan-take) ----------------------
# OpenAI-compatible endpoint. The ingest uses it to turn Portuguese headlines into
# natural Korean. Without it, the pipeline falls back to free MyMemory MT.
# Recommended free options (pick one):
#   • Cerebras:   LLM_BASE_URL=https://api.cerebras.ai/v1     LLM_MODEL=zai-glm-4.7
#   • OpenRouter: LLM_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1   LLM_MODEL=deepseek/deepseek-chat
#   • Groq:       LLM_BASE_URL=https://api.groq.com/openai/v1 LLM_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile
# LLM_API_KEY=
# LLM_BASE_URL=https://api.cerebras.ai/v1
# LLM_MODEL=zai-glm-4.7

# Optionally narrow/expand the news query (defaults to a football-biased query).
# NEWS_QUERY=Palmeiras (Verdão OR Brasileirão OR Libertadores OR futebol)
# Set DISABLE_MT=1 to skip the free MyMemory translation fallback.
# DISABLE_MT=

# --- Football data (real squad photos) -----------------------------------------
# API-Football (api-football.com) — free tier. Used for the real current squad
# photos. (Its free plan blocks the current SEASON for standings/fixtures, which
# is why standings/matches use ESPN instead.)
# API_FOOTBALL_KEY=
# API_FOOTBALL_HOST=v3.football.api-sports.io
# THESPORTSDB_KEY=   # optional alternative sports source

# --- Caching --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Server-side in-memory cache TTL (seconds) for adapter responses. Default 300.
# DATA_CACHE_TTL_SECONDS=300
